15:T4ab,Critical conflict detected: Internal brochure shows 'Merineum Hernia Mesh' under FILAPROP brand, but external manufacturer evidence clearly distinguishes Merineum as a separate dual-layer composite mesh product (PP+PLC with anti-adhesive barrier) distinct from Filaprop (heavyweight monofilament PP mesh). The slug 'merineum-hernia-mesh' and brochure heading 'Filaprop Merineum' suggest product naming confusion or catalog merge error. Merineum is a tissue-separating composite mesh for ventral repairs; Filaprop is a standard/heavyweight PP mesh for general hernia repair. These are different product lines with different materials, structures, and clinical indications. The SKU examples (PPM611, PPMS611) appear to be Filaprop codes, not Merineum codes. Current classification lists Filaprop characteristics (lightweight, inguinal/ventral/incisional) which conflicts with Merineum's specific composite dual-layer ventral focus. Requires urgent review to determine if: (1) this is actually Merineum product incorrectly labeled as Filaprop, (2) catalog merged two distinct products, or (3) naming convention issue. Recommend split into separate product pages if both products exist in portfolio.7:["$","div",null,{"className":"min-h-screen bg-[#0A0A0A] text-white","children":[["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org/\",\"@type\":\"Product\",\"name\":\"Merineum Hernia Mesh\",\"description\":\"Lightweight polypropylene mesh for hernia repair procedures. Available in flat and 3D configurations for inguinal, ventral, and incisional hernia repairs.\",\"brand\":{\"@type\":\"Brand\",\"name\":\"Meril\"},\"category\":\"Hernia Mesh\",\"manufacturer\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"Meril Life Sciences\"},\"offers\":{\"@type\":\"AggregateOffer\",\"offerCount\":\"1\",\"lowPrice\":\"0\",\"priceCurrency\":\"INR\",\"availability\":\"https://schema.org/InStock\"}}"}}],["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-7xl 